cs.HCI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper focuses on the development of an interactive visualization system for interpreting large-scale deep learning models and results. This involves addressing unique design challenges posed by the complexity and wide variety of models deployed in industry, and the large-scale datasets that they used. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HCI (Human-Computer Interaction), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
